President Trump held a press conference in the Oval Office to discuss the recent passing of the border security bill and the signing of the criminal justice reform bill, known as the FIRST STEP Act. He thanked the House Republicans for their support and expressed his hope that the Senate would also pass the bill. The President emphasized the importance of border security in addressing issues such as drug trafficking and human trafficking. He highlighted the bipartisan nature of the criminal justice reform bill and thanked his daughter Ivanka and son-in-law Jared Kushner for their role in pushing for the legislation. Several politicians and individuals affected by the criminal justice system also spoke at the press conference, expressing their gratitude for the passage of the bill.